        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We require the full polarization mode of Band 7 to detect the polarization of the dust continuum.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>In Cycle 3 observations, the largest angular size of the source must be less than FWHM/3 of the primary beam (ALMA Technical Handbook). The 12-m antenna beamsize is 18.4 arcsec at Band 7 and thus the angular size of the source must be less than 6.1 arcsec. The source size is within 5 arcsec. Therefore, the largest angular size is feasible.
As discribed in Scientific Justification, we require the angular resolution high enough to resolve the structure of 0.3 x 1.0 arcsec in size in both Stokes Q and U images. The required angular resolution is 0.12 arcsec in this proposal, which safely resolves the structure.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We require the sensitivity to detect the polarization degree of 0.3 % at the peak of the continuum emission. To detect the polarization with 3 sigma, we need the S/N ratio of 1000 at the peak. With the required angular resolution, 0.12 arcsec, the peak flux density is expected to be 23.2 mJy/beam, which is calculated from the cycle 0 continuum data. Therefore, we require the sensitivity of 23.2/1000 [mJy/beam] = 23.2 [?Jy/beam]. We set the sensitivity to be 22 ?Jy/beam because the estimated observing time is the same as the case of the sensitivity of 23.2 ?Jy/beam, which is 6 hours in total.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
